  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nYannick requested a demonstration of design mode capabilities versus traditional image generation. Manus generated a visual comparison showing design mode's system-oriented approach that produces reusable components, typography, layouts and interconnected elements rather than isolated static images. The core distinction established: image generation produces pixels while design mode constructs systematic design frameworks.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUnderstanding the fundamental differences between design mode and image generation to clarify the superior capabilities of systematic design approaches\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nGenerated a comparative visual demonstrating design mode's system-based approach versus traditional image generation's pixel-focused output\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [visual comparison] Design Mode vs Image Generation — Side-by-side illustration showing isolated pixel generation versus systematic design component creation\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Focus on system vs pixel distinction as core differentiator\n- Use visual contrast to demonstrate conceptual difference\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Visual demonstration effectively communicated abstract concept\n- Clear distinction between approaches established\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Design mode's value lies in systematic reusability rather than visual quality alone\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How to implement design mode in practice\n- What tools support systematic design generation\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Explore practical implementation of design mode\n- Develop systematic design generation workflows\n---\nUID: 7GZyO6nWR8oltDSIOBOoxv | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0100\n"
